[3
From: Peter_Cowen@ncsu.edu
I have just returned from 5 days in the UK last week, and I was
struck, long before I read these postings, on how clearly the broadcast
media had tied the _E. coli_ cases to the mud. There were many reports
hammering home the message that the disease came from the muddy cow pasture.
If anything were going to ruin a case control study, it was a barrage of
media
information linking disease to a particular causative entity, i.e. mud.
There is no evidence that the ProMED-mail posting was the origin of what
was broadcast on the airways.
--
Peter Cowen
ProMED-mail Moderator
Peter_Cowen@ncsu.edu
